'''Armando Chavarría Barrera''' (27 August 1956 – 20 August 2009) was a [[Mexican people|Mexican]] politician affiliated with the [[Party of the Democratic Revolution]]. He served as Senator of the [[LVIII Legislature of the Mexican Congress|LVIII]] and [[LIX Legislature of the Mexican Congress|LIX]] Legislatures of the Mexican Congress representing [[Guerrero]] and as Deputy of the LVII Legislature.<ref>{{cite web|title=Perfil del legislador|url=http://sil.gobernacion.gob.mx/Librerias/pp_PerfilLegislador.php?SID=&Referencia=547988|publisher=Legislative Information System|accessdate=27 April 2014}}</ref>

On 20 August 2009 Chavarría was murdered when he was leaving his house.<ref>{{cite news|last=Cervantes|first=Juan|title=Matan a presidente del Congreso de Guerrero|url=http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/notas/620752.html|accessdate=27 April 2014|newspaper=El Universal|date=20 August 2009}}</ref>

